1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the capacity of time-varying channels, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of feedback in communication systems, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of a communication system with feedback, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of adaptive coding in a communication system, which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves mathematical analysis and optimization of a communication system, which can be viewed as a computational engineering problem.
